<br>
1-3 mage very weak but isnt everyone? =)<br>
<br>
4-24 mage is very strong getting nukes that rival wizard nukes and pets that are on par with old world experience mobs of the same lvl.<br>
<br>
24-34 is very weak time for the mage. Most mages I have spoken to mark this as one of the most difficult stages for the mage. Pets really dont improve all that much and our nukes are way to weak by the time we reach lvl 28 to 29.<br>
<br>
34-44 this is a good time for the mage. DD power takes a giant leap forward and at lvl 39 pets get regen and the lvl 44 pet quads.<br>
<br>
44-50 This is the stage where mages become uber gods for there lvl. lvl 49 pets are awesome and when you combine that with the lvl 44 shock and lava bolt there is no other offensive class as powerful at this stage of the game. (wishes these days would come back /sigh)<br>
<br>
Wezloc<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I really have two questions.  Is this a fair categorization?  Seems like it to me, but then I have spent so much time post-50, I am loathe to try to speak with authority on behalf of younger mages.<br>
<br>
Second, what <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>are</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> the class balance issues that effect magicians pre-50 and at what levels are they felt?  Are there specific problems for pre-50 <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that are missed by discussions dominated by post-50 <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->?  Are there some specific remedies or proposals that might be lost in the crush to improve post 50 or post 60 <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
ArchAbuser of EZCodes<br>
