<br>
Then again my mage was my first character to experience those levels so perhaps I didn't know where to hunt effectively. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eriol>Eriol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(4/1/02 12:21:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  He's Completely Right from what I know</span><hr size=1> I was powerful from lvl 4-24.  And the period from lvl 24-34 is hell.  I have basically been sucking exp from any group i've been in.  Magicians just don't help much in the group because our nukes are so weak.  Just the other day a lvl 29 Enchanter was out-nuking me!  By a lot!  His were 280+, and my best one WITH focus was 211!  I know I am just sucking off exp until i hit lvl 34, where my nukes get good again.<br>
<br>
I honestly can't comment on higher lvls, only being lvl 32 right now, but soloing good exp mobs is also almost impossible at these lvls.  There are good places, but they are usually not safe either.  And yellows?  Good luck finding any to solo relatively safely.<br>
<br>
The core of the problem is that magicians do NOT get a significant damage upgrade at lvl 24.  The lvl 20 bolt does almost as much dmg as the lvl 24 DD, and we don't get another DD or bolt until lvl 34, at which time we get both.  So we basically spend almost half of our lives, and more than half of our time 20-34, with about the same dmg nuke!  If I had to fix it, I would move our lvl 34 DD DOWN to lvl 29, and keep the bolt at lvl 34.  Then we get incremental dmg increases through the lvls.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp.<br>
<br>
