<br>
Kids these days...don't know how lucky they are.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I tried to remember back to the key events when I was a younger <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and here is what stood out for me.  Early on, my pet was more powerful than me, and gained enormously by being handed a rusty two handed weapon.  Even when they stopped being yellow or even, they were still better than the mobs I faced.  And I could melee well enough.<br>
<br>
I'd say this period ended around 20th or so.<br>
<br>
I remember <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>really</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> feeling the weakness of my pets just before the next spell circle for some time, maybe until 39th.<br>
<br>
From 39th to 50th, life was good.  All I had to do was find a camp with blues that no one was using, learn to pull and avoid adds, and I was set.  And I was good at that too.  I would poke my head into underpopulated zones, look for odd corners or static spawns, and master them.<br>
<br>
That is when I started training my friends to respect the awesome power that is a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Once I mastered the camp, I would invite others, especially those lower level than me in the guild that were having trouble grouping with the big guys, and show them my camp, and start pulling.  It rocked.<br>
<br>
I don't remember ever being unsatisfied with my nukes, just my middle-level, end-of-circle pets, as I said.  I also remember being disappointed that I could not make more money selling summoned items, not even bandages.<br>
<br>
Based on what I remember then, I conclude that pets might need a boost from something like 20th or 24th up to 34th or so, in order that they do not peter out as the next spell circle approaches.<br>
<br>
Based on what others have written here, some adjustments of nukes might be plausible, keeping in mind that I have also heard <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Wizards</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> complain that our nukes are sometimes too close or even better than theirs at low levels.  But then improving <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Wizards</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> at those levels seems okay to me.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Senior ArchMage, Ancient Fellowship, Xev<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umodauth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>modauth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(4/1/02 5:45:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Magician class balance pre-51?</span><hr size=1> Well I can throw a bit of perspective maybe on this. 42 Days played time and level 46 yes it's sad. A 4 month break during that and the fact that I spend alot of time just mucking around causing trouble and stirring my other guild members up <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  None the less I remember the hardest time I had as a mage was grinding from 34 - 44. At one point when I was level 42 a friend of mine in the guild literally dragged me through that level and 43. I would get bored of the soloing and go spend some time looking for a group to no avail. A higher mage in the guild more or less took me aside and just said &quot; stick it out until 44 and you'll see&quot; So I took his advice and stuck it out until then. Dinged 44 and took off with new pets to kill some more faction with Kaladim Citizen's ( as if I can get it any worse ). Only had the fire pet at the time and figured I might as well try it out. I barely got 2 nukes off. I was amazed because after all that time I actually felt powerful again and wasn't always on the verge of gating or clicking the sow potion and moving as fast as I can as far away as possible.  Now all I can do is just look forward to level 49 and the pets there but this time, <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I've got them already and on level 48 ding I will be carrying them with me in a backpack at all times <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <br>
<br>
As far as balancing and tweaking I would have to completely agree that from 24ish to 34, 39ish its a must. Maybe even to 44. I went through so many alt's because it was just so I guess frustrating during that level frame to play a mage. Not getting groups, just roaming around looking for that perfect camp to get that I could pull just one mob with Malise and stand back and toss a nuke and 2 heals on the pet. 42 days played time to level 46, my warrior alt has 3 days played at level 31. Kind of sickening I think <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Last thing is I have trolled these boards for months and months on end even when I took a break from EQ in general and have to see that even from the worst ( foci item nerf ) to the very best , ( seeing very constructive and thought out opinions ), this message board has to be one of the very greatest resources for the magician class as a whole.  I don't see how any proper magician can't come to these boards and the magecompendium and not walk away knowing at least one new thing or seeing another side to something. I know I do.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1178<br> <font color=#333333>(4/1/02 6:58:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  An aside...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Last thing is I have trolled these boards for months and months<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Just soze ya noze fer da foocher, trollin iz win youse make da comment like:<br>
<br>
MAGICIANS SUCK!  STFU AND PLAY A REAL CLASS LIKE ROGUE!<br>
<br>
Juz soze yu kin see how much chit yu kin stir up.<br>
<br>
What you did is commonly called <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> lurking</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: reading the boards and not posting.  It is generally a very good idea to lurk for a while on a board to learn its tenor and limits before posting.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, what you did could also be considered <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> trawling</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: casting your net wide across the board to scoop up all that yummy knowledge <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (even if some of what passes for facts around here is a bit fishy)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
One comment on your experience.  Sometimes its not knowing where to hunt.  That becomes tighter generally as you rise levels.  At first level, you can solo yellow giant rats and fire beetles, but as you rise, you wind up having to select creatures that are more and more less powerful than you.  For example, at 60th, I can only reliably solo things that are just barely blue to me.  If <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Planes of Power</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> adds another ten levels, then at some point I will likely be completely unable to solo for experience.<br>
